programme.title: 100 Women
programme.desc: Film director Chlo Zhao is the only woman of colour to win an Oscar for best director, with her poetic drama Nomadland - and to this day, only one of three women to have won the coveted award. Her films focus on outcast communities: indigenous people, cowboys and nomads. Most recently, she has entered the Marvel Universe to direct the most diverse film in the franchise so far. Her upcoming film, Hamnet, tells the story of Agnes, the wife of William Shakespeare, and will be released later this year. Zhao sat down with BBC 100 Women to talk about being a woman behind the camera and how the film industry in Hollywood is still shaped by men - something she's trying to change

programme.title: A Banquet
programme.desc: A widowed mother is radically tested when her teenage daughter insists a supernatural experience has left her body in service to a higher power. Mystery thriller, starring Sienna Guillory and Jessica Alexander

programme.title: Monster House
programme.desc: A boy becomes obsessed with a sinister elderly neighbour living in a creepy old house. On Halloween night, he and two friends discover the chilling truth - the house is alive and eats anything that comes too close, including children. Animated comedy horror, with the voices of Mitchel Musso, Sam Lerner, Spencer Locke, Steve Buscemi, Maggie Gyllenhaal and Jason Lee

programme.title: Shrek Forever After
programme.desc: The grumpy ogre longs for his simple life as a feared monster, so strikes a deal with magical trickster Rumpelstiltskin to get back to the way things were. However, he soon finds there is a catch - he ends up stuck in an alternate world where none of his friends know who he is and where Rumpelstiltskin has become the kingdom's tyrannical ruler. Animated comedy, with the voices of Mike Myers, Eddie Murphy and Cameron Diaz

programme.title: Mr Popper's Penguins
programme.desc: A workaholic businessman always puts his job before his family until he receives an unexpected inheritance from his explorer father - six penguins. He abandons his plan to offload the birds to a zoo when he finds his kids love them, and sets about turning his New York apartment into a suitable habitat. Family comedy, starring Jim Carrey, Carla Gugino and Angela Lansbury

programme.title: Cutthroat Island
programme.desc: A tough female pirate enlists the help of an educated slave in finding the three parts of a map leading to buried treasure. However, one of the pieces is in the hands of her cruel uncle, and she also has to find the loot before her crew mutinies or the British Navy catches up with her. Swashbuckling adventure, starring Geena Davis, Matthew Modine, Frank Langella and Maury Chaykin

programme.title: Daddy's Home 2
programme.desc: Having settled their differences, Brad and Dusty's newfound friendship is put to the test when their respective fathers - one gentle, the other overly macho - arrive for the Christmas holidays, forcing them to change their plans. What starts as a break at a fun-filled trip to a luxury resort turns into something far more chaotic. Comedy, starring Will Ferrell, Mark Wahlberg, Mel Gibson and John Lithgow

programme.title: The Last Duel
programme.desc: In medieval France, squire Jacques Le Gris secures a captaincy destined for knight Jean de Carrouges. To rub salt into fresh wounds, Jacques' promotion includes land intended for his rival. Jean canters off to war and returns to his wife Marguerite, who claims she was sexually assaulted by Jacques. Ridley Scott's epic drama based on a book by Eric Jager, starring Adam Driver, Jodie Comer, and Matt Damon and Ben Affleck (who also worked on the screenplay)

programme.title: Blue Bayou
programme.desc: As a Korean-American man raised in the Louisiana bayou works hard to make a life for his family, he must confront the ghosts of his past as he discovers that he could be deported from the only country he has ever called home. Drama, directed by and starring Justin Chon, with Alicia Vikander

programme.title: The Gravedigger's Wife
programme.desc: When his wife rapidly becomes ill, gravedigger Guled has to find a way to make the money for the surgery that will save her life. As a poor man who can't read or write, lucrative jobs are hard to come by and Guled has to return to the village and family he ran from. Khadar Ahmed's drama, starring Omar Abdi and Yasmin Warsame. In Somali

programme.title: Outcast of the Islands
programme.desc: A clerk in a South Seas trading post gets involved in smuggling, betraying his employers and bringing about his own tragic end. Drama, starring Ralph Richardson and Trevor Howard

programme.title: Jubal
programme.desc: Rancher Shep Horgan takes in injured drifter Jubal, and offers him a job. However, a jealous ranch hand takes a dislike to the new arrival, and tries to persuade Horgan that Jubal is having an affair with his wife. Western, starring Glenn Ford, Rod Steiger, Valerie French, Charles Bronson and Ernest Borgnine

programme.title: Sink the Bismarck!
programme.desc: Fact-based Second World War drama, charting the mission to track down and eliminate the pride of the German fleet, a fearsome battleship devastating British vessels in the North Atlantic, orchestrated by a British naval officer recovering from his wife's death in an air raid. Starring Kenneth More, Dana Wynter, Laurence Naismith and Karel Stepanek

programme.title: The Desert Rats
programme.desc: A Scottish army officer is placed in command of a unit of Australian troops given the task of defending Tobruk against overwhelming German forces, led by the renowned general Rommel. Second World War adventure, starring Richard Burton, Robert Newton and James Mason, reprising his role as Rommel from The Desert Fox

programme.title: Footloose
programme.desc: A rebellious, hip-swinging student from the city moves to a small religious community, where he instantly clashes with an old-school fire-and-brimstone preacher - who has banned dancing and rock 'n' roll because he considers them immoral. Drama, starring Kevin Bacon, Lori Singer, John Lithgow, Chris Penn, Dianne Wiest and Sarah Jessica Parker

programme.title: Kingsman: The Secret Service
programme.desc: A streetwise teenager is taken under the wing of his dead father's old colleague, an agent working for a super-secret spy organisation. Will the youngster turn out to be a chip off the old block by proving useful during a battle against a twisted, hi-tech genius? Action comedy based on a comic book, starring Colin Firth, Taron Egerton and Samuel L Jackson

programme.title: Patriot Games
programme.desc: Former CIA agent Jack Ryan foils an assassination attempt by an IRA splinter group, killing one of the terrorists in the process. However, he becomes caught in a lethal game of cat-and-mouse with the dead man's revenge-seeking brother. Thriller based on Tom Clancy's novel, starring Harrison Ford, Sean Bean, Samuel L Jackson, Richard Harris and James Earl Jones, reprising his role from earlier Clancy adaptation The Hunt for Red October

programme.title: Primal
programme.desc: A hunter and collector of rare and exotic animals bags a priceless white jaguar for a zoo, but the ship bearing his precious cargo has two predators caged in its hold - the cat, and a political assassin being extradited to the Unites States. After the assassin breaks free - and then frees the jaguar - the hunter feverishly stalks the ship's cramped corridors in hot pursuit of his prey, right up until the unpredictable climax. Action thriller, starring Nicolas Cage, Famke Janssen and Kevin Durand

programme.title: Against the Wind
programme.desc: A Belgian priest living in exile in Britain during the Second World War becomes a secret agent for the Allies, but his first mission is a disaster, leading to the capture of a resistance leader. Four soldiers are sent into occupied France to rescue the insurgent, but begin to realise they have a traitor in their midst. Thriller, starring Jack Warner and Simone Signoret

programme.title: The Smallest Show on Earth
programme.desc: A newly married couple inherit a dilapidated cinema and its incompetent staff and resolve to transform its fortunes. They soon find, however, that their hopes for the future are far more difficult to realise than anticipated. Basil Dearden's comedy, starring Bill Travers, Virginia McKenna, Peter Sellers, Margaret Rutherford, Bernard Miles and Leslie Phillips

programme.title: The Mouse That Roared
programme.desc: The leaders of the tiny European duchy of Grand Fenwick decide to solve their bankruptcy problem by declaring war on the USA. They confidently expect to lose and thereby qualify for economic aid - but the plan takes an unexpected turn for the worse when the Americans surrender. Comedy, starring Peter Sellers in three roles, with Jean Seberg, William Hartnell, David Kossoff and Leo McKern

programme.title: The Quiet Man
programme.desc: An American prizefighter retires after killing an opponent in the ring, and returns to his Irish roots in a village in Galway, where he falls for a local woman. Unfortunately, their romance is hampered by a conflict with her brother over a property matter. John Ford's Oscar-winning romantic comedy drama, starring John Wayne, Maureen O'Hara, Victor McLaglen, Barry Fitzgerald and Ward Bond

programme.title: Romancing the Stone
programme.desc: A romantic novelist goes in search of her kidnapped sister in the steamy jungles of South America, only to become the target of a villainous general who demands as a ransom the valuable treasure map in her possession. Help is at hand in the form of a craggy daredevil fortune hunter, who has his eye on a share of the profits. Comedy adventure, starring Michael Douglas, Kathleen Turner and Danny DeVito

programme.title: Kingsman: The Golden Circle
programme.desc: Having saved the world once, secret agents Eggsy and Merlin join forces with their US counterparts to bring down a psychotic femme fatale. Thankfully they are assisted by a veteran hero brought back from the dead, and cross paths with a kidnapped Elton John and a couple of killer robot dogs along the way. Director Matthew Vaughn's comedy adventure sequel, starring Taron Egerton, Colin Firth, Mark Strong and Julianne Moore

programme.title: Paul
programme.desc: An alien held captive in a top-secret American military base escapes and hides out in the van of two English comic-book geeks on a tour of UFO hotspots. The wisecracking extraterrestrial enlists the duo's help in getting back to his spaceship, but they are soon pursued by government agents and unwittingly become kidnappers. Sci-fi comedy, starring Simon Pegg and Nick Frost, with the voice of Seth Rogen

999: On the Front Line
programme.desc: On the night shift in Coventry, paramedics are concerned that a pregnant woman with severe stomach pains could be having a potentially life-threatening ectopic pregnancy. In Birmingham, a paramedic team treat an 84-year-old man who has collapsed in his bedroom and been lying on the floor for 13 hours. With his blood pressure dangerously low, it's a race against time to get him upright and into hospital. In Worcester, paramedics treat a four-year-old boy whose mother sought help when he developed a rash and began fighting for breath

programme.title: 24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: A patient with a rare condition is rushed in to St George's in south west London, struggling to breathe. Her husband tells the story of their child's struggle with leukemia. A woman with a history of emphysema comes to St George's after complaining to her GP of chest pains, and a 19-year-old medical student has an abnormal growth on her femur

programme.title: 24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: Fifteen-year-old Gus is rushed to the department after going over the handlebars of his bike. Patricia, 73, is in extreme pain, having dislocated her shoulder months ago. Bryan arrives with a swollen and painful hand after falling while walking his daughter's dog

programme.title: Food Unwrapped
programme.desc: Jimmy Doherty journeys to Japan to unleash the power of wasabi, Matt Tebbutt finds out which foods generate the most wind, and Kate Quilton asks if there is there really any difference between dog and cat food

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Mark and Caroline want a bolthole on Spain's stunning Orihuela Costa that works for all the family and is close to the golf courses. Scarlette Douglas shows them what their 100,000 budget can secure

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Trevor from London fell in love with the island of Gozo in Malta when he first holidayed there five years ago, and now he plans to relocate there once he's retired. Jonnie Irwin lines up five great properties for Trevor's 150,000 budget, but it's a big decision so Trevor brings his sister Janet along to help

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Danni Menzies helps Colin and Elspeth from Edinburgh search for a holiday home in Menorca, which they can enjoy well into their retirement with their family

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Jo and Darrell from south-west London are looking for a holiday home on the Balearic Island of Menorca to enjoy with their two young children and Darrell's grown-up son. They run their own busy human resources company together so cannot wait to find a bolthole to relax in and have some quality time as a family. With a budget of 300,000 Danni Menzies is on hand to show them five properties around the south of the island

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Paul and Bev have been married for a decade and now wish to realise their dream of relocating to Torrevieja, Spain. With a maximum budget of 100,000 and a long list of family and friends ready to come out and visit, this extremely sociable pair want a property with enough space for guests as well as a music room for musician Paul. Jean Johansson sets out to help find them an appropriate property

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Paul and Clare are looking for a holiday home in central Portugal, with Paul's passion for biking a key part of their search. Jasmine Harman sets out to find a place that can double up as a bikers' retreat, on their 120,000 budget

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: The competition comes from in and around Brighton. The first host, 47-year-old radio presenter Guy, plans a musical evening with a Mexican menu and an air guitar competition. His guests are 26-year-old recruitment company director Emma, 28-year-old pilot Tim, 38-year-old personal trainer Hannah and 50-year-old 'love doctor' Monti. Guy hosts a hilarious evening with lessons in love, surprising revelations and a dessert that doesn't go to plan

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: It is the second day in and around Brighton, and bubbly 26-year-old Emma is hosting a beach-themed dinner party in the hope of winning the 1,000 cash prize. After a day of forgotten ingredients and culinary calamities, Emma has some questions up her sleeve to help her find out more about 'love doctor' Monti. Dutch pilot Tim is also feeling the love, as a bromance begins to blossom

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: The competition continues in and around Brighton, as Dutch pilot Tim draws on his travel experience to produce an international menu. After a turbulence-free day in the kitchen, Tim continues to charm his guests, especially DJ Guy

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Personal trainer Hannah reveals quite a lot more about herself to her guests. There are no shortage of shocks and surprises as layer after saucy layer is peeled away from the usually quiet and reserved host, but there's sauciness of a different kind when one guest annoys the others by defiantly adding their own condiments to each of the three courses

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: The final night of competition in and around Brighton, sees 50-year-old 'love doctor' Monti try to cast his spell over his guests in an attempt to win the 1000 cash prize. While Monti tries to spread the love, Tim really puts his foot in it as his compliment to Hannah gets well and truly lost in translation

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.sub-title: Oaklea Barns Guest House Season 2018, Episode 1
programme.desc: The competition begins at Oaklea Barns Guest House on Merseyside, where Mandi Magee and her partner Paul Green think their impeccable standards will wow their rivals. Guest Ian loves his room but is perplexed by plastic on the lampshades, while Mark and Natalie are thrown by a loose loo. During an exercise in falconry, Dave and Sanchia cry foul when chirpy Mandi rules the roost. At breakfast, Mandi makes it clear she thinks she can't be beaten, but Dave and Sanchia say they'll rise to the challenge

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.sub-title: The Guest House Worsthorne Season 2018, Episode 2
programme.desc: The second visit is to The Guest House Worsthorne in Lancashire, where partners Dave Rogers and Sanchia Crossley aim to win over their guests

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: For the third visit of the week, the group heads to the Sleeperdorm Backpacker Hotel in Newcastle, where Ian Nicholls hopes his guests will enjoy his cheap and cheerful concept

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.sub-title: The Parsonage Hotel and Spa Season 2018, Episode 4
programme.desc: The B&B battle continues at the Parsonage Hotel and Spa near York, a 55-room country manor which wows the guests with its size, although Mandi's high cleaning standards are not met

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.sub-title: Fri 19 Jan 2018: Payment Day Season 2018, Episode 5
programme.desc: The final day of the competition sees the B&B owners meet for the last time to find out what they've been paid and to settle some scores. Oaklea Barns is first, and hosts Mandi and Paul want answers from Mark and Natalie, which ends up fanning flames
